  <front>
   <head>SONNET [06] VI. To Hope.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">OH, Hope! thou soother sweet of human woes!</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How shall I lure thee to my haunts forlorn!</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For me wilt thou renew the wither'd rose,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And clear my painful path of pointed thorn?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ah come, sweet nymph! in smiles and softness drest,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Like the young hours that lead the tender year;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Enchantress come! and charm my cares to rest: —</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Alas! the flatterer flies, and will not hear!</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A prey to fear, anxiety and pain,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Must I a sad existence still deplore?</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Lo! — the flow'rs fade, but all the thorns remain,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">'For me the vernal garland blooms no more.'</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Come then 'pale Misery's love!' be thou my cure,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And I will bless thee, who tho' slow art sure.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
